utputs on the mesh and patch decomposition. The goal is not to build the final wave engine; it is to make operator quality, pulse localization, and coarse-versus-fine behavior inspectable and regression-testable before Milestone 10 begins.\nagent_tickets/milestone_6_surface_discretization_tickets.md:128:- The report includes at least pulse initialization, boundary-mask inspection, coarse-versus-fine projection or reconstruction views, and a compact summary of operator quality metrics with pass, warn, or fail semantics.\nagent_tickets/milestone_5_geometry_pipeline_tickets.md:124:Add offline preview tooling that consumes already-built local geometry bundles and generates an inspection-friendly report for one or more root IDs. The tool can be a script, notebook, or small library-backed report generator, but it should standardize how the team compares raw mesh, simplified mesh, skeleton, surface graph, and patch graph views without requiring live FlyWire access.\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-001_Define_a_versioned_geometry_asset_contract_for_multiresolution_morphology_bundles/stdout.jsonl:9:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_3\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"rg -n \\\\\\\"manifest|mesh|skeleton|graph|asset\\\\\\\" src scripts tests docs config schemas -g '\\\"'!data/**'\\\"'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"schemas/milestone_1_experiment_manifest.schema.json:3:  \\\"$id\\\": \\\"https://example.local/schemas/milestone_1_experiment_manifest.schema.json\\\",\\nconfig/local.yaml:12:  meshes_raw_dir: data/interim/meshes_raw\\nconfig/local.yaml:13:  skeletons_raw_dir: data/interim/skeletons_raw\\nconfig/local.yaml:14:  processed_mesh_dir: data/processed/meshes\\nconfig/local.yaml:15:  processed_graph_dir: data/processed/graphs\\nconfig/local.yaml:16:  manifest_json: data/processed/asset_manifest.json\\nconfig/local.yaml:102:meshing:\\nconfig/local.yaml:103:  fetch_skeletons: true\\ndocs/milestones.md:17:- **Program