ssets so the simulator does not talk to FlyWire live during runtime.\\n\\n## Why this repo uses selective meshing\\n\\nThe female whole brain is the structural scaffold, but the final simulation should only keep a small subset in a mesh-wave state at once. That matches a multiresolution strategy:\\n\\n- whole brain mapped,\\n- selected circuit meshed,\\n- only active patches numerically updated.\\n\\n## Artifact contracts\\n\\n### Subset-selection contract\\n\\nMilestone 4 subset generation writes one artifact bundle per named preset under\\n`data/interim/subsets/<preset>/`:\\n\\n- `root_ids.txt`: simulator-facing root-id list\\n- `selected_neurons.csv`: filtered registry rows for the preset\\n- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\\n- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\\n- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\\n\\nThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\\nso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\\n\\n### Geometry handoff contract\\n\\nPer neuron, the processed output includes:\\n\\n- `root_id.ply` simplified mesh\\n- `root_id_graph.npz` adjacency + Laplacian + patch mask\\n- `root_id_meta.json` counts and preprocessing metadata\\n\\nThose files are the handoff point into a later simulator.\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\nagent_tickets/runs/20260321T170513Z/FW-M5-001_Define_a_versioned_geometry_asset_contract_for_multiresolution_morphology_bundles/stdout.jsonl:108:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_64\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"nl -ba docs/pipeline_notes.md | sed -n '20,80p'\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"    20\\t\\n    21\\tMilestone 4 subset generation writes one artifact bundle per named preset under\\n    22\\t`data/interim/subsets/<preset>/`:\\n    23\\t\\n    24\\t- `root_ids.txt`: simulator-facing root-id list\\n    25\\t- `selected_neurons.csv`: filtered registry rows for the preset\\n    26\\t- `subset_stats.json`: graph counts, role counts, and boundary summaries\\n    27\\t- `subset_manifest.json`: resolved selection rules plus the selected neuron roster\\n    28\\t- `preview.md`: lightweight Markdown/Mermaid preview for quick inspection\\n    29\\t\\n    30\\tThe active preset also refreshes the path named by `config.paths.selected_root_ids`\\n    31\\tso downstream pipeline steps can switch subsets without code changes.\\n    32\\t\\n    33\\t### Geometry handoff contract\\n    34\\t\\n    35\\tMilestone 5 uses the versioned geometry bundle contract\\n    36\\t`geometry_bundle.v1`. One canonical library path builder owns the\\n    37\\tfilenames below, and both `scripts/02_fetch_meshes.py` plus\\n    38\\t`scripts/03_build_wave_assets.py` use it directly.\\n    39\\t\\n    40\\tPer neuron, the bundle layout is:\\n    41\\t\\n    42\\t- `config.paths.meshes_raw_dir/<root_id>.ply`: raw mesh\\n    43\\t- `config.paths.skeletons_raw_dir/<root_id>.swc`: raw skeleton\\n    44\\t- `config.paths.processed_mesh_dir/<root_id>.ply`: simplified mesh\\n    45\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_graph.npz`: surface graph\\n    46\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_patch_graph.npz`: patch graph\\n    47\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_descriptors.json`: derived descriptor sidecar\\n    48\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_qa.json`: QA sidecar\\n    49\\t\\n    50\\t`config.paths.manifest_json` records the bundle contract version, dataset,\\n    51\\tmaterialization version, meshing-config snapshot, and per-root asset\\n    52\\tstatuses/paths.\\n    53\\t\\n    54\\tCompatibility shim:\\n    55\\t\\n    56\\t- `config.paths.processed_graph_dir/<root_id>_meta.json` is still written as\\n    57\\t  a legacy metadata pointer so older consumers can keep reading the prior\\n    58\\t  sidecar name during migration.\\n\",\"e