ch activation entropy\\ndocs/milestones.md:875:- patchification sensitivity\\ndocs/milestones.md:1000:- whole suites run from manifest files  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1060:- downstream / upstream graph overlays  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1066:- graph visualization  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1092:- manifest schema\\ndocs/milestones.md:1121:- mesh/patch representation choice\\ndocs/milestones.md:1215:### 1\\\\. Subset manifest contract\\ndocs/milestones.md:1229:- patch graphs  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1255:- per-neuron / per-patch state summaries  \\ndocs/milestones.md:1322:- or a **dependency graph / Kanban structure**\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:18:  locked_hypothesis: \\\"Morphology-resolved surface dynamics constitute an additional intraneuronal computational degree of freedom, capable of shaping circuit input-output transformations through distributed spatiotemporal state on neuronal structure.\\\"\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:19:  operational_claim: \\\"In a connectome-constrained Drosophila visual motion circuit, adding a morphology-resolved surface state should produce small but reproducible, geometry-dependent departures in shared circuit observables relative to fair point/reduced-neuron baselines.\\\"\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:48:    description: Detect a nonzero shared-output effect centered on null-direction suppression when morphology-bound surface dynamics are present.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:56:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, with the intact-minus-baseline gap contrasted against the shuffled condition\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:57:    expected_relationship: The surface-wave model produces a small but reproducible shared-output departure relative to the matched baseline.\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:75:    comparison: surface_wave/intact versus matched baseline/intact, then intact versus shuffled\\nconfig/milestone_1_design_lock.yaml:96:    comparison: (surface_wave/in